      "message": "So, in this CL I didn\u0027t want to really mess w/ the behavior. The asserts in the following if-blocks definitely assume that the two buffers don\u0027t overlap and would still fire even with the return fix.\n\nWhen \u0027other\u0027 has a color part it is probably safe to copy the color into \u0027this\u0027 op. However, if it has a stencil component we would also need to check the \u0027fStencilInsideMask\u0027 field. Given how seldom we hit these cases, since people aren\u0027t really screaming about the asserts, I didn\u0027t think the extra complexity was going to be worth it.",
