      "message": "I\u0027d be comfortable with fixing it in this CL, because now that it\u0027s coming back to me, I remember these asserts I had added in an early draft of the stencil+color combining changes (before they were separate ops). Initially, I had thought I needed to keep them distinct, and then realized at the end that we can just merge single buffer ops into a kBoth op if they have the same area.\n\nI think it\u0027d be easy to not add your if-check and delete the asserts. I don\u0027t think we need to check the stencil-inside-mask field, since that\u0027s just the stencil state value we are clearing to, so the new op\u0027s value is preserved, just like we do for the color buffer. Right?",
